The paper focuses on image inpainting using deep learning methods, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed model is a generative model, which involves learning from data and generating new samples, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of consistency loss and style extraction, which are common techniques in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
